metatags.twitter:title: Sydney, Australia. 21 August 2021. An anti COVID-19 lockdown protest at Victoria Park has resulted in multiple arrests but few protesters in attendance. The event ran in conjunction with similar protests on the same day in cities around Australia, notably Melbourne, where much larger crowds gathered. The Sydney demonstration was notable for its large police presence of 1400 officers. Victoria Park is situated at Broadway and City Road near Sydney University. Traffic was brought to a stand-still during parts of the demonstration. Pictured: an arrest on City Road Stock Photo - Alamy
